criteria.driver_alignment:
Discover — framed the GameStop case to investigate behavioral drivers;  
Implement — wrote and ran code to analyze the event (data/AR/CAR);  
Reflect — interpreted behavioral mechanisms (herding, confirmation bias, overconfidence) and linked them to outcomes.

Represent — presented data and stated the market-model framework for AR calculation;  
Implement — wrote and ran code to fetch data, estimate OLS (alpha, beta) and compute abnormal returns;  
Validate — verified historical price data and reported regression statistics and significance tests.

Discover — identified the event and the need to verify baseline prices;  
Implement — estimated the market-model via OLS and reported alpha, beta, R², t-stat and p-value;  
Validate — compared/verified historical price data using external sources (NASDAQ and Yahoo Finance).
